Overview

The 2015 Audi A5 is basically a coupe version of the A4 sedan. It is offered in Malaysia in two- and four-door guise. Priced between RM357,900 and RM402,900, engine option for both the variants are limited to a 2.0-litre turbo four-pot. The four-door vairant goes to fight directly against the BMW 4-Series Gran Coupe, while the two-door takes care of the Infiniti Q60, Lexus RC, Mercedes-Benz C-Class Coupe and also the BMW 4-Series Coupe.

Powered by a 2.0-litre TFSI four-cylinder turbocharged engine, the Malaysian-spec A5s output 225hp and 350Nm of torque. The latter arrives at an early 1,500rpm and remains until 4,500rpm. A seven-speed S tronic dual-clutch automatic gearbox is employed to send power to all four wheels. It can complete the century sprint in 6.4 seconds, before reaching a top speed of 250km/h. 

On the outside, the machines from Ingolstadt features Xenon adaptive headlights, LED daytime running lights, front and rear fog lights, and power folding side mirrors with LED turn signals.

Interior and convenience highlights include Nappa leather electric sports front seats with embossed S line logo, leather wrapped three-spoke multifunctional steering wheel with paddle shifters, matt brushed aluminium accents and three zone automatic air-conditioning. Besides that, there is also Audi Drive Select module with four modes, Audi hold Assist, a tyre pressure monitoring system, light and rain sensor, cruise control and automatic start/stop.

Safety wise, the 2015 Audi A5 Coupe 2.0 TFSI comes loaded with six airbags, electronic stabilisation program, traction control, ABS with EBD and Brake Assist and ISOFIX anchor points. 
